HEADWORD: Exercisible
<hw>Ex"er*ci`si*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Capable of
being exercised, employed, or enforced; <as>as, the authority of a
magistrate is <ex>exercisible</ex> within his
jurisdiction</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

